# Git sync after changes

When you finish making changes to this project:

1. Run `git status` and commit all relevant changes (do not commit secrets).
2. Push to `origin main` immediately — do not wait for the user to ask.
3. Confirm the push succeeded and report the commit hash briefly.

The live site is GitHub Pages at https://cebenestelli-miti.github.io/Matches/ — pushing `main` deploys updates.

If there are no changes to commit, say so and verify the branch is up to date with `origin/main`.
